    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That seems like a very specific way to judge it. If we look at it through a realist lens, though, a quick strike that removes a hostile actor and prevents a genocide without a long-term occupation could be seen as a huge win for national interest. Are you saying that any intervention that doesn't result in a Western-style democratic stability is inherently a failure?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
