      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A realist perspective would indeed view the removal of a hostile dictator as a significant short-term win for US national interest. However, the definition of \"success\" in foreign policy is not solely about regime change; it must also account for the resulting security environment. When an intervention creates a power vacuum that breeds extremism, it undermines long-term security interests, making the overall outcome a strategic failure regardless of the initial tactical success.",
      "source": "target",
